      <div class="panel-body">
				<h4>
				This project was written to gain a better understanding of how the magic of Ruby on Rails works. By utilizing Ruby metaprogramming, some of the basic functionalities of Rails such as mass-assignment protection, creating reader and writer methods for instance variables, and the awesome power of associations were replicated.
				</h4>
				<h4>
				I really enjoyed this project as it allowed me to get a better understanding of how Ruby on Rails works under the hood. New technology has always been created to make things easier, but also forces you to be bound by its constraints. By knowing how it works, instead of being bound by the program, I have confidence that I can modify the boundaries or create my own.
				</h4>
